        <h4>Local science / research</h4>
        <p>The better a place is cared for, the more cures, discoveries, and innovations it holds.</p>
        <p>Pharmaceuticals have a history of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bioprospecting#Biopiracy">biopiracy</a> in places of rich biodiversity  taking discoveries and innovation, without sharing incomes with the communities themselves.</p>
        <!-- <p>World-changing cures, science, and discoveries are waiting in our forests, mountains, rivers, and oceans.  Communities are capable of conducting this research and making these findings themselves, which exist because of thousands of years of their stewardship.</p> -->
        <p>Communities are capable of conducting this research and making these findings themselves, which we owe to thousands of years of their stewardship.</p>

